<paragraph id="7A0AC81D23783A7986E5BE8984699CEA" blockId="41.[211,309,168,192]" box="[211,309,168,192]" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">
<emphasis id="48C1140F23783A7986E5BE8984699CEA" box="[211,309,168,192]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7A0AC81D23783A7986E5BEEE81DC9D4D" blockId="41.[211,1172,207,360]" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">
The description and illustration of 
<taxonomicName id="BDB5B39E23783A79846BBEF186539CCD" baseAuthorityName="Hu and Fu" baseAuthorityYear="1985" box="[605,783,208,231]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nanjiangensis">
<emphasis id="48C1140F23783A79846BBEF186539CCD" box="[605,783,208,231]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">E. nanjiangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sub 
<taxonomicName id="BDB5B39E23783A79857BBEEE81349CCD" authorityName="Hu and Fu" authorityYear="1985" box="[845,1128,207,231]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Heteropoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nanjiangensis">
<emphasis id="48C1140F23783A79857BBEEE81349CCD" box="[845,1128,207,231]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">Heteropoda nanjiangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by 
<bibRefCitation id="1E24B5EC23783A7986E5BED184FC9D2D" author="Hu JL &amp; Fu YP" box="[211,416,239,263]" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479" pagination="86 - 93" refId="ref23803" refString="Hu JL, Fu YP. 1985. On two species of Heteropodidae (Araneae) from Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, China. Bull Shadong Univ. 3: 86 - 93." type="journal article" year="1985">Hu and Fu (1985)</bibRefCitation>
as well as examination of the type series match fully with 
<typeStatus id="A50E76BF23783A798206BECE81C89D2D" box="[1072,1172,239,263]" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">holotype</typeStatus>
male of 
<taxonomicName id="BDB5B39E23783A798701BF3184E89D0D" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[311,436,272,295]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="potanini">
<emphasis id="48C1140F23783A798701BF3184E89D0D" box="[311,436,272,295]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">E. potanini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Further females (along with sympatric males) examined from around the type locality, revealed conspecifity of them with the 
<typeStatus id="A50E76BF23783A7985A9BF0E815F9D6D" box="[927,1027,303,327]" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">holotype</typeStatus>
female of 
<taxonomicName id="BDB5B39E23783A79824CBF1184399D4D" authorityName="Hu and Fu" authorityYear="1985" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Heteropoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nanjiangensis">
<emphasis id="48C1140F23783A79824CBF1184399D4D" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">E. nanjiangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, this species is proposed as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="BDB5B39E23783A7985C9BF7181259D4D" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[1023,1145,336,359]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="potanini">
<emphasis id="48C1140F23783A7985C9BF7181259D4D" box="[1023,1145,336,359]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">E. potanini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
